###########################################################################
#  text_smcp_active - GSUB smcp consumer-side activation.                  #
#                                                                          #
#  Phase 2 of the OpenType smcp/onum work.  When the env var               #
#  LOUT_SVG_FONT_FEATURES is set (here: forced by run_compare.sh by way of #
#  recognising this snippet's name) the SVG back-end routes every word    #
#  with an active substitution through <path d="..."/> emission instead   #
#  of <text>.                                                              #
#                                                                          #
#  The standard URW Type 1 base35 set has no OpenType GSUB table, so a     #
#  test-only synthetic mode (LOUT_SVG_FONT_FEATURES_SYNTH=smcp,onum)       #
#  maps each lowercase letter to its uppercase glyph entry inside the     #
#  same font and each digit to its named-glyph entry.  This proves that   #
#  the consumer path emits <path> elements end to end without requiring  #
#  an OTF/CFF font with real smcp data in Lout's AFM tree.                 #
#                                                                          #
#  Verification (independent of pixel diff): the .svg output for this     #
#  snippet must contain at least one "<path d=" substring inside a word   #
#  region.  See tests/run_compare.sh for the env-var trigger.             #
###########################################################################

@SysInclude { doc }
@Doc @Text @Begin
@PP
small caps abc and figures 0123.
@End @Text
